=head2 ReadCacheConfiguration => L<Paws::FSX::OpenZFSReadCacheConfiguration>

The configuration for the optional provisioned SSD read cache on file
systems that use the Intelligent-Tiering storage class.


=head2 RemoveRouteTableIds => ArrayRef[Str|Undef]

(Multi-AZ only) A list of IDs of existing virtual private cloud (VPC)
route tables to disassociate (remove) from your Amazon FSx for OpenZFS
file system. You can use the API operation to retrieve the list of VPC
route table IDs for a file system.


=head2 ThroughputCapacity => Int

The throughput of an Amazon FSx for OpenZFS file system, measured in
megabytes per second (MB/s). Valid values depend on the DeploymentType
you choose, as follows:

=over

=item *

For C<MULTI_AZ_1> and C<SINGLE_AZ_2>, valid values are 160, 320, 640,
1280, 2560, 3840, 5120, 7680, or 10240 MB/s.

=item *

For C<SINGLE_AZ_1>, valid values are 64, 128, 256, 512, 1024, 2048,
3072, or 4096 MB/s.

=back



